Local TV personality Terry Pheto will be attending the French Open in Paris as a guest of Longines The A United Kingdom actress wrote on Twitter: “I’m so honoured and thrilled to be attending the French Open at Ronald Garros with the Longines family. Looking forward to witnessing brilliant performances and Longines’ elegant hospitality.” The prestigious French Open is a major tennis tournament held over two weeks at the Stade Roland-Garros in Paris, France. The announcement comes after the 37-year-old was unveiled as the June cover star for Marie Claire magazine. READ MORE: Terry Pheto wins two more international awards Longines’ brand ambassadors include tennis superstars Steffi Graf and Andre Agassi. – The Juice